defs.docs:
indicatif is a library for Rust that helps you build command line
 interfaces that report progress to users.  It comes with various
 tools and utilities for formatting anything that indicates progress.

defs.name: FormattedDuration
defs.docs: Wraps an std duration for human basic formatting.

defs.name: HumanDuration
defs.docs: Wraps an std duration for human readable formatting.

defs.name: HumanBytes
defs.docs: Formats bytes for human readability

defs.name: DecimalBytes
defs.docs: Formats bytes for human readability using SI prefixes

defs.name: BinaryBytes
defs.docs: Formats bytes for human readability using ISO/IEC prefixes

defs.name: ProgressIterator
defs.docs: Wraps an iterator to display its progress.

defs.name: progress
defs.docs:
Wrap an iterator with default styling. Attempt to guess iterator
 length using `Iterator::size_hint`.

defs.name: progress_count
defs.docs: Wrap an iterator with an explicit element count.

defs.name: progress_with
defs.docs: Wrap an iterator with a custom progress bar.

defs.name: ProgressBarIter
defs.docs: Wraps an iterator to display its progress.

defs.name: ProgressDrawTarget
defs.docs: Target for draw operations

defs.name: stdout
defs.docs: Draw to a buffered stdout terminal at a max of 15 times a second.

defs.name: stderr
defs.docs: Draw to a buffered stderr terminal at a max of 15 times a second.

defs.name: stdout_with_hz
defs.docs: Draw to a buffered stdout terminal at a max of `refresh_rate` times a second.

defs.name: stderr_with_hz
defs.docs: Draw to a buffered stderr terminal at a max of `refresh_rate` times a second.

defs.name: stdout_nohz
defs.docs: Draw to a buffered stdout terminal without max framerate.

defs.name: stderr_nohz
defs.docs: Draw to a buffered stderr terminal without max framerate.

defs.name: to_term
defs.value: fn (term: Term, refresh_rate: impl Into<Option<u64>>) -> ProgressDrawTarget
defs.docs: Draw to a terminal, optionally with a specific refresh rate.

defs.name: hidden
defs.docs: A hidden draw target.

defs.name: is_hidden
defs.docs: Returns true if the draw target is hidden.

defs.name: ProgressBar
defs.docs: A progress bar or spinner.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new progress bar with a given length.

defs.name: hidden
defs.docs: Creates a completely hidden progress bar.

defs.name: with_draw_target
defs.docs: Creates a new progress bar with a given length and draw target.

defs.name: with_style
defs.docs: A convenience builder-like function for a progress bar with a given style.

defs.name: new_spinner
defs.docs: Creates a new spinner.

defs.name: set_style
defs.docs: Overrides the stored style.

defs.name: enable_steady_tick
defs.docs: Spawns a background thread to tick the progress bar.

defs.name: disable_steady_tick
defs.docs: Undoes `enable_steady_tick`.

defs.name: set_draw_delta
defs.docs: Limit redrawing of progress bar to every `n` steps. Defaults to 0.

defs.name: tick
defs.docs: Manually ticks the spinner or progress bar.

defs.name: inc
defs.docs: Advances the position of a progress bar by delta.

defs.name: is_hidden
defs.docs: A quick convenience check if the progress bar is hidden.

defs.name: println
defs.docs: Print a log line above the progress bar.

defs.name: set_position
defs.docs: Sets the position of the progress bar.

defs.name: set_length
defs.docs: Sets the length of the progress bar.

defs.name: inc_length
defs.docs: Increase the length of the progress bar.

defs.name: set_prefix
defs.docs: Sets the current prefix of the progress bar.

defs.name: set_message
defs.docs: Sets the current message of the progress bar.

defs.name: reset_eta
defs.docs: Resets the ETA calculation.

defs.name: reset_elapsed
defs.docs: Resets elapsed time

defs.name: finish
defs.docs: Finishes the progress bar and leaves the current message.

defs.name: finish_at_current_pos
defs.docs: Finishes the progress bar at current position and leaves the current message.

defs.name: finish_with_message
defs.docs: Finishes the progress bar and sets a message.

defs.name: finish_and_clear
defs.docs: Finishes the progress bar and completely clears it.

defs.name: abandon
defs.docs: Finishes the progress bar and leaves the current message and progress.

defs.name: abandon_with_message
defs.docs: Finishes the progress bar and sets a message, and leaves the current progress.

defs.name: set_draw_target
defs.docs: Sets a different draw target for the progress bar.

defs.name: wrap_iter
defs.docs: Wraps an iterator with the progress bar.

defs.name: wrap_read
defs.docs: Wraps a Reader with the progress bar.

defs.name: MultiProgress
defs.docs: Manages multiple progress bars from different threads.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new multi progress object.

defs.name: with_draw_target
defs.docs: Creates a new multi progress object with the given draw target.

defs.name: set_draw_target
defs.docs: Sets a different draw target for the multiprogress bar.

defs.name: set_move_cursor
defs.docs: Set whether we should try to move the cursor when possible instead of clearing lines.

defs.name: add
defs.docs: Adds a progress bar.

defs.name: join
defs.docs: Waits for all progress bars to report that they are finished.

defs.name: join_and_clear
defs.docs: Works like `join` but clears the progress bar in the end.

defs.name: ProgressBarIter
defs.docs: Iterator for `wrap_iter`.

defs.name: ProgressBarRead
defs.docs: Reader for `wrap_read`.

defs.name: ProgressStyle
defs.docs: Controls the rendering style of progress bars.

defs.name: default_bar
defs.docs: Returns the default progress bar style for bars.

defs.name: default_spinner
defs.docs: Returns the default progress bar style for spinners.

defs.name: tick_chars
defs.docs: Sets the tick character sequence for spinners.

defs.name: tick_strings
defs.docs: Sets the tick string sequence for spinners.

defs.name: progress_chars
defs.docs: Sets the three progress characters `(filled, current, to do)`.

defs.name: template
defs.docs: Sets the template string for the progress bar.

defs.name: get_tick_char
defs.docs: Returns the tick char for a given number.

attributes.value: deprecated(since = "0.13.0", note = "Deprecated in favor of get_tick_str")

defs.name: get_tick_str
defs.docs: Returns the tick string for a given number.

defs.name: get_final_tick_char
defs.docs: Returns the tick char for the finished state.

attributes.value:
deprecated(since = "0.13.0", note =
             "Deprecated in favor of get_final_tick_str")

defs.name: get_final_tick_str
defs.docs: Returns the tick string for the finished state.
